HEADWORD: Bourse
<hw>Bourse</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>bourse</ets> purse, exchange, LL. <ets>bursa</ets>, fr. Gr.<?/
skin, hide, of which a purse was usually made. Cf. <er>Purse</er>,
<er>Burse</er>.]</ety> <def>An exchange, or place where merchants,
bankers, etc., meet for business at certain hours; esp., the Stock
Exchange of Paris.</def>⟦br⟧
